      <description>&lt;p&gt;Iâ€™ve been making a lot more use of my digital photo frame since I moved into my flat but a fair few of the photos I want to make use of are portrait orientation whilst the majority are landscape.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For a load of photos Iâ€™ve gone thru them and manually made them landscape by using a method I noticed that Youâ€™ve Been Framed use when viewers send in mobile footage shot in the wrong orientation for tv. The technique is to enlarge a second copy of the image/video as a background layer to fit the width of the landscape orientation and blur the background.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I figured as Iâ€™d want to do this to a lot of images over time Iâ€™d make a script to do so. So using Photoshopâ€™s Actions Iâ€™ve done so and thought Iâ€™d share it:Â &lt;a href=&#34;https://mikedixson.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Landscapify-Mike-Dixson.atn_.zip&#34;&gt;Landscapify â€“ Mike Dixson.atn&lt;/a&gt;Â Hereâ€™s how to load the actions into your PhotoshopÂ &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.imphotography.com/downloads/installactions.htm&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.imphotography.com/downloads/installactions.htm&#34;&gt;http://www.imphotography.com/downloads/installactions.htm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://mikedixson.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Mikes-Photoshop-Actions.atn_.zip&#34;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Instructions&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Open Image&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;In the Actions Window click on Landscapify&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Click the Play Icon &amp;gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;When prompted for the new canvas size enter the current width as the height and the current height as the width&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Click Ok (if prompted that clipping will occur click Ok to that too&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Youâ€™re done ðŸ™‚&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;div id=&#39;gallery-3&#39; class=&#39;gallery galleryid-337 gallery-columns-2 gallery-size-thumbnail&#39;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;figure class=&#39;gallery-item&#39;&gt; &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#39;gallery-icon portrait&#39;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a href=&#39;https://mikedixson.com/landscapify-adjusting-portrait-photos-for-landscape-frames/3d-summit-day-1-6386-pre-landscapified/&#39;&gt;&lt;img width=&#34;150&#34; height=&#34;150&#34; src=&#34;https://mikedixson.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/3D-Summit-Day-1-6386-pre-landscapified-150x150.jpg&#34; class=&#34;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; aria-describedby=&#34;gallery-3-340&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption class=&#39;wp-caption-text gallery-caption&#39; id=&#39;gallery-3-340&#39;&gt; Portrait &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;figure class=&#39;gallery-item&#39;&gt; &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#39;gallery-icon landscape&#39;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;a href=&#39;https://mikedixson.com/landscapify-adjusting-portrait-photos-for-landscape-frames/3d-summit-day-1-6386-landscapified/&#39;&gt;&lt;img width=&#34;150&#34; height=&#34;150&#34; src=&#34;https://mikedixson.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/3D-Summit-Day-1-6386-landscapified-150x150.jpg&#34; class=&#34;attachment-thumbnail size-thumbnail&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; aria-describedby=&#34;gallery-3-341&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption class=&#39;wp-caption-text gallery-caption&#39; id=&#39;gallery-3-341&#39;&gt; Landscapified &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Hope itâ€™s useful to you.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Mike&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;</description>
